mainEntity.name: When is the cheapest time to visit Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: If you're a more budget-conscious traveler, then you may want to consider traveling to Seattle between December and February, when hotel prices are generally the lowest. Peak hotel prices generally start between June and August.

review.name: Sites and Sounds of Seattle.
review.reviewBody: Great tour to learn history about Seattle and see some picturesque sites. Our guide James was very knowledgeable.

review.name: Outstanding Experience
review.reviewBody: Guide was outstanding ~ James went out of the way to take extra time to show us additional sites!!!  The trip was fantastic!!

review.name: I got "Lucky" in Seattle
review.reviewBody: My husband, brother, sister-in-law, and I ended our 7-day Alaska cruise in Seattle.  I booked the 3.5 hour "Show Me Seattle" tour.   Did I get "lucky" in Seattle!  Lucky Lane was our tour guide.  Lucky picked us up at the pier, showed us more sights than we expected in Seattle, got us to the airport on time, took pictures of our group, and kept us laughing all the time.  Outstanding tour guide, very knowledgeable.  Thank you Lucky.  Highly recommend this tour--made us want to go back to Seattle!

review.name: Well worth it
review.reviewBody:
Keith was an incredible tour guide.  We were entertaining clients who had never been  Seattle.  Keith took us to all the iconic Seattle sites and surprised us with several stops which included picturesque views of Seattle, secret waterfall gardens and beautiful wildlife scenes.   
He provided incredible details, history and stories along the way.  He held our attention to entire time. 
It was well-worth the cost for a private tour and one our guests will be talking about for years to come.
Thanks, Keith!!
